subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis . Within Gonatocerini, the species of
Cosmocomoidea
are distinguished by the following combination of features: subantennal sulci strongly converging and close together at mouth margin (
Fig. 43
); ocellar triangle with 2 setae (
Fig. 43
); pronutm with lobes abutting (
Fig. 49
); dorsellum rhomboidal, with anterior and posterior margins not parallel (
Fig. 49
); fore wing with microtrichia behind venation usually absent (
Fig. 19
) but, if present, only on one surface (
Fig. 20
) or less dense than beyond venation; propodeum with two submedian carinae ( Figs 17 , 49 ).
